text: I am exhausted with seeing Johnny Depp, "the character." It was fun at first 10 plus years ago, but we're now at a junction where I miss seeing Depp, the actor, who didn't have to use or rely on absurd facial hair, accents, quirky expressions, and oddity, as his only means to convey a character. His characters have largely become forgettable now instead of unique and/or ground breaking because they all seem to come from the same stew. It would be nice to see him actually play some sort of normal human being grounded in reality.
